a0209c8b3a52b5a7b76d4303cb51c8f41c00e8ed36749a1748fd2ff29b068a91  result/rootfs.tar.gz
# Rebaselined 2026-07-15 after making the rootfs repack deterministic.
#
# build/rootfs/apply-stages.nix and build/rootfs/tarball.nix now tar with
# --sort=name --mtime=@1700000000 (SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH) and pigz/gzip -n, so the
# archive entry order, timestamps and gzip header no longer vary across
# rebuilds. Verified with `nix build .#os-image --rebuild` (exit 0, no "differs").
# --numeric-owner is kept and --owner/--group are intentionally NOT forced to 0
# (the rootfs legitimately contains non-root files, e.g. /home/vcap = 1000/1000).
#
# KNOWN REMAINING GAP (does not affect this hash while the base is cached, but
# breaks true end-to-end reproducibility if the base rootfs is rebuilt from
# scratch): the base image ships 12 install-time ephemeral files whose CONTENT
# is random per build and which survive into the os-image —
#   /etc/machine-id, /etc/nvme/hostid, /etc/nvme/hostnqn,
#   /etc/ssh/ssh_host_{rsa,ecdsa,ed25519}_key(.pub),
#   /var/cache/ldconfig/aux-cache, /var/log/{dpkg,alternatives}.log
# These need scrubbing in the base build (tarball.nix) to be fully reproducible.
# Tracked separately because removing SSH host keys / machine-id is a
# security/behaviour change that must regenerate on first boot.
#
# The previous hash (4eee73a9...) was stale after the co-location refactor.
